\b EQUIPMENT\par
\b0\par
Figure it out for yourself, my lad,\par
You've all that the greatest of men have had,\par
Two arms, two hands, two legs, two eyes\par
And a brain to use if you would be wise.\par
With this equipment they all began,\par
So start for the top and say, "I can."\par
\par
Look them over, the wise and great\par
They take their food from a common plate,\par
And similar knives and forks they use,\par
With similar laces they tie their shoes.\par
The world considers them brave and smart,\par
But you've all they had when they made their start.\par
\par
You can triumph and come to skill,\par
You can be great if you only will.\par
You're well equipped for what fight you choose,\par
You have legs and arms and a brain to use,\par
And the man who has risen great deeds to do\par
Began his life with no more than you.\par
\par
You are the handicap you must face,\par
You are the one who must choose your place,\par
You must say where you want to go,\par
How much you will study the truth to know.\par
God has equipped you for life, but He\par
Lets you decide what you want to be.\par
\par
Courage must come from the soul within,\par
The man must furnish the will to win.\par
So figure it out for yourself, my lad.\par
You were born with all that the great have had,\par
With your equipment they all began,\par
Get hold of yourself and say: "I can."\par
\par
\par
-Edgar A. Guest\par
